    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A flexible support or base used for photographic negatives and motion picture film from 1890 to the 1950s. It is made of cellulose nitrate with camphor as a plasticizer; it is unstable and flammable.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
